-- BNP Paribas Hires Swiss Rock’s Vogt to Cater to German Clients
-- B y   F a b i o   B e n e d e t t i - V a l e n t i n i   a n d   E l e n a   L o g u t e n k o v a
-- 2012-06-04T17:11:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-04/bnp-paribas-hires-swiss-rock-s-vogt-to-cater-to-german-clients.html
BNP Paribas (BNP)  (Suisse) SA, the Swiss
unit of France’s largest bank, hired Swiss Rock Asset Management
AG’s Bernhard Vogt to cater to German private-banking and
corporate-banking clients.  Vogt will be based in Switzerland, Julie Beuter, a Paris-
based spokeswoman for BNP Paribas SA, said by telephone today,
declining to provide further details on his past career and
future functions.  Vogt, formerly Swiss Rock’s head of  customer service  for
private clients and family offices, has three decades of
experience in caring for wealthy individuals, according to the
Zurich-based’s asset manager’s  website . He previously held
positions at Deutsche Bank AG, Credit Suisse Group AG and UBS
AG, the website said.  To contact the reporters on this story:
